{"books":{"13":{"id":"4789","title":"That Mother-in-Law of Mine","description":"<p>Here we were, only a month married, and spending our honeymoon at a most charming summer resort, where there was no excuse for getting out of patience. Everything was beautiful and attractive: Little hotel, strange to say, quite delightful; no fault to find with surroundings and accommodations; my darling Bessie, as sweet as an angel and determined to be happy and to make me happy; everything, in short, calculated to give us a long summer of delight. <br\/>That is, if Bessie had only been an orphan. But there was her mother, who had joined us on our summer trip, after the first two weeks of unalloyed happiness, and threatened to accompany us through life. (excerpt from chapter 1)<\/p>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.gutenberg.org\/ebooks\/30270","language":"English","copyright_year":"1879","num_sections":"14","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/4789","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/that_mother_in_law_of_mine_ck_librivox\/that_mother_in_law_of_mine_ck_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/that-mother-in-law-of-mine-by-anonymous\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"2:40:10","totaltimesecs":9610,"authors":[{"id":"19","first_name":"","last_name":"Anonymous","dob":"","dod":""}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/details\/that_mother_in_law_of_mine_ck_librivox","sections":[{"id":"47935","section_number":"1","title":"Bessie and I and Bessie's Mother","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"505","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"5244","display_name":"Carolin Ksr"}]},{"id":"47936","section_number":"2","title":"Courting the Mother","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"793","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"5244","display_name":"Carolin Ksr"}]},{"id":"47937","section_number":"3","title":"Our Marriage","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"551","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_i